About
A simple counter app using html,css,js and go(for backend). link to repo We serve the frontend using go's http server package. http://localhost:8080". 1.If we click the '+' button, it increments the counter.
1.Create project directory: counter-web-app. go mod init counter counter. touch counter.go counter.go with the below lines: package main
import ( "fmt" "net/http" )
func main() { fs := http.FileServer(http.Dir("./public/")) http.Handle("/", fs)
fmt.Println("Server is running on http://localhost:8080") http.ListenAndServe(":8080", nil) }
Explanation: fs := http.FileServer(http.Dir("./public/"))
Creates a file server that serves the public folder. http.Handle("/", fs)
